gomodel:SYNGO_589  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: SV31 (TMEM163) is a SV membrane protein with 6 predicted transmembrane helices (Fig.1).\n\nFig.4: Immunoblotting after subcellular fractionation of synaptosomes: Rat and mouse crude synaptic fractions exhibited a band at 31kDa using a polyclonal peptide antibody to the N-terminal aa48-63 (Fig. 4a). Fractions obtained from a sucrose density gradient revealed a bimodal distribution of SV31 similarly to Synaptotagmin-1 with an enrichment in the low density SV fraction and the denser membrane fractions (which contain both plasma membrane and SVs that attach to the plasma membrane) (Fig.4b).\n\nAntibody: No KO-control, but no signals were obtained from Western Blots of total brain homogenates when the pre-immune serum was applied.\n\nOf note: Only a very small proportion of synaptosomes were labelled. Gold particles were bound only to SVs, whereas other membranes were unlabelled.\n\nAntibody: polyclonal peptide antibody to the N-terminal aa48-63 generated in the study. No KO-control, but no signals were obtained from Western Blots of total brain homogenates when the pre-immune serum was applied. No immunostaining was obtained with preimmune serum or when only the secondary antibody was applied for IHC.. Experimental description: Figure legend Fig. 4: Crude vesicle fractions from rat and mouse brain reveal a band at 31 kDa.\n\n6/6/2017 Pim\nData for both rat and mouse tissues are presented in Fig.4. The species will be chosen dependent on the species information in ticket #744. --> *rat* species was selected" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_589" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

